text: Bjarne Øverhaug (3 November 1927 – 20 August 1996) was a Norwegian journalist and politician for the Labour Party. He served as a deputy representative to the Parliament of Norway from Hedmark during the terms 1969-1973 and 1973-1977\. In total he met during 16 days of parliamentary session. He resided in Tynset and was a journalist in Hamar Arbeiderblad. ==References== Category:1927 births Category:1996 deaths Category:People from Tynset Category:Norwegian journalists Category:Deputy members of the Storting Category:Labour Party (Norway) politicians Category:Hedmark politicians Category:20th-century journalists
